text: Serena Williams had hardly been
challenged at the US Open heading into
Sunday's final against Victoria Azarenka
Williams had lost only 16 games in six
matches and her serve had been broken
only twice but she knew she would get a
fight from Azarenka her closest rival on
the tour who had won two of their last
three matches last year in the Open
final they played a tense and dramatic
three set instant classic this year's
meeting would bring more of the same
extremely windy conditions at Arthur
Ashe Stadium added an unpredictable
element to the match Williams and
Azarenka traded breaks of served to open
the match as each try to adjust the wind
particularly bothered Williams and she
struggled to judge her shots and her
footwork but Williams managed to break
Azarenka to go up six five then steadily
held her serve to win the set Williams
quickly went up by two breaks in the
second set but Azarenka rallied to even
the score Williams twice served for the
championship and was broken both times
as the set went to a tiebreaker
Williams saved two set points in the
tiebreaker but Azarenka converted the
third to send the match to a third set
despite her second set collapse Williams
was composed and focused to begin the
third set she gained the edge in the
fourth game when Azarenka double-faulted
on a break point Azarenka was broken
again two games later giving Williams
yet another chance to serve for the
title this time she did not let the
opportunity go
Williams leapt for joy over and over
after Azarenka's last shot sailed out to
close a 7-5 6-7 6-1 victory Williams won
her fifth US Open Championship and her
17th Grand Slam title overall one behind
Chris Evert and Martina Navratilova
for fourth on the career list
